               <head>Commentary on the Exodus by Shemu᾿el ben Mosheh al-Magrebi</head>
               
               
               
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <summary>The commentary on the book of Exodus (fragments).</summary>
                  
                  
                  
                  <textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr" otherLangs="he"/>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="1r" to="41v"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush shemot</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">פירוש שמות </title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <author>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf.org/viaf/305238133">Shemu᾿el ben Mosheh, al-Magrebi </persName>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="he" key="viaf.org/viaf/305238133">שמואל בן משה, המערבי</persName>
                     
                     
                     
                     </author>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Part of an Arabic commentary on Exodus 32:24-26, 31-32, 33:3-4, 35:2-40:34.</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The 'questions and answers', i.e. she'elot u-teshuvot, begin on folio 28r.</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The words of the biblical text are introduced by the formula: <q>קאל אלנץ אלכרים</q>.</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Contains fragments of the same author's introduction to the weekly portions, see folios 25r-25v and 26r-26v. </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                     
                     
                     
                     <filiation>Some parts of the manuscript correspond to Or 2483, George Margoliouth, Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, 4 vols (London: British Museum, 1899-1935; vols I-III repr. 1965); IV, Introduction, Indexes, ed. by Jacob Leveen (London: British Museum, 1977), no. 395..</filiation>
                  
                  
                  
                  </msItem>
               
               
               
               </msContents>
               
               
               
